  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to compare the clinical efficacy of multimedia audiovisual training to hands
      on &quot;practice till perfect&quot; training for pediatric and emergency medicine residents'
      procedural skills. This initial study will explore the success rates on infant lumbar
      puncture and child intravenous access skills in post-graduate year one pediatric residents.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
